# LLM Navigator Freshness

## Hard requirement

Any change to public-facing structure, onboarding instructions, command contracts, runtime model, deployment behavior, or operational documentation must update `llms.txt` in the same change.

## Required updates

- If new files/folders are added, include them when they affect onboarding orientation.
- If files are removed/renamed, remove or update stale links immediately.
- If commands or env conventions change, update the command matrix in `llms.txt`.
- If public/private scope changes, update the exposed/excluded policy immediately.

## Exclusions

This rule does not apply to edits fully contained in:
- `.manual/*`
- `.paas/*`

## Validation

Before handing off, confirm:
1) `llms.txt` contains valid links and section order.
2) no closed/private directories are exposed by default.
3) navigation still starts from `README.md` and `docs/README.md`.

